cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and coding, specifically multiple description coding and scalable coding. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also involves multimedia applications, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible category. The use of random variable substitution and the study of achievable rate-distortion regions suggest cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as additional categories. Finally, the study of the role of refinement layer in coding suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
